This paper deals with machine translation and neural encoder-decoder architectures, which are commonly studied in the fields of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training data and pivot-based sequence generation, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its model on tasks related to transliteration and captioning, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
